{
  "answer": "The description appears in *Bang-E-Dara Part 2* by Allama Iqbal, chapter 16 (\"Kali\").\n\n> It sips on splendor in the tavern of morn,  \n> Its life from the **Sun's own goblet** is born.[^1]  \n>   \n> Before the Sun, it **tears its breast apart**,  \n> What blissful pleasure for its tiny heart![^2]  \n>   \n> [...][^3]  \n>   \n> Let me behold my Sun, though far it seems,  \n> And **like a bud**, be **wrapped within its beams**.[^4]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/16-kali/translation/#p-ae86d8).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/16-kali/translation/#p-99fffa).\n\n[^3]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, [chapter](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/16-kali/translation/).\n\n[^4]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/16-kali/translation/#p-44ef90).",
